A **do-while loop** is similar to the while loop, except that it guarantees the code inside the loop will execute at least once, regardless of whether the condition is true or false. Syntax: ```js
do {
    // code to execute
} while (condition);
``` * The block of code is executed first, then the condition is checked. If the condition is true, the loop continues.

code_playground.code:
let secretNumber = 5;
let guess;

do {
  guess = 5;  // Simulating player input
  console.log("You guessed: " + guess);

  if (guess === secretNumber) {
    console.log("Correct! You won!");
  } else {
    console.log("Wrong, try again.");
  }
} while (guess !== secretNumber);

