**Mistake 3: Not Updating the Counter Variable** If the counter variable is not updated inside the loop, it may result in an infinite loop. Error Example: ```js
let a = 1;
let counter = 1;
while (counter < 3) {
    a = a + 1;
    console.log(a);
}
console.log("End");
``` * **Fix**: Always update the counter variable to prevent an infinite loop.

code_playground.code:
let counter = 1;
while (counter < 3) {
    console.log(counter);
    counter++;  // Update counter inside loop
}
console.log("End");

// Without update (infinite loop - commented out to prevent freeze):
// let attempts = 1;
// while (attempts < 5) {
//     console.log("Attempt " + attempts);
//     // Missing: attempts++
// }

// With update (correct):
let attempts = 1;
while (attempts < 5) {
    console.log("Attempt " + attempts);
    attempts++;  // Update counter
}
console.log("Validation complete");

